<br>
No one told me 51 is a hell level.  That's okay.  A full Wyvern quad gives me about half a bubble of blue xp.  Not bad, I guess.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I've been working in Sol B some trying to farm some runed mithril bracers for my level 52 druid that someone gave me that was totally butt naked.  I've had friends, including my favorite tank, bard, and cleric, join me along with the somewhat-now-clothed droood.<br>
<br>
Actually, last night, while I was AFK, my friends got me not just one but *two* golden chitin bracers!  My int is now 210.<br>
<br>
The bonus there is I can give up the stein.  Alas, the stein is a wondeful item, but I am glad to give it up.  This means Spankda is gonna be a two-fisted wielder.  On the right hand I'll have my Staff of Temperate Flux.  On the left hand, I'll have my Solist's Icy Wand. <br>
<br>
Yeah baby.  The wand can go in a secondary slot.  Woot!  No more switching between the wand and the staff.  I'll have buttons for each.  I've actually used the wand as a distance guaging device, but with the cast time, it's not efficient.<br>
<br>
Okay.  Yvolcarn looks just like any other normal Wyvern.  I pulled him with my staff yesterday without realizing it until I got the Snared, Snared, Snared, Resist message.  Hmm?  One resisted?  Turn around and target the resisting critter.  Yvolcarn is on target.<br>
<br>
/shout Yvolcarn to SS zone!  Sorry.<br>
<br>
I'm grateful he doesn't summon unless damaged.  Really.<br>
<br>
Moral of this little story:  Make sure you're getting a Wyvern and not Yvolcarn when agro'ing a quad.<br>
<br>
Atol's Spectral Shackles beats Bonds of Force hands down.  I will never go back.  The only issue I have with Atol's is it appears to have a larger radius of effect than BoF does.  About 25 feet for Atol's versus 20 feet for BoF, according to Caster's Realm.<br>
<br>
What does this mean?  It means Spankda is snared 90% of the time in Sol B when he snares the critters.  Yeah.  I snare myself a lot.  Be careful with Atol's folks.  Just a friendly warning.<br>
<br>
On another note:  I became a hero yesterday by giving a shadow rapier to a chick in my guild who was getting her JBoots.  Basically, doing a /w all GUILD showed me a bunch of folks in their 30's and 40's in SK.  What's up in SK?  I asked.  Shadowmen.  Chick is getting her Jboots.  <br>
<br>
Cool!<br>
<br>
About an hour later.  You all still there?  Yeah.  No rapier dropping!<br>
<br>
Are they no drop?  No.<br>
<br>
About an hour later.  I gate to G'Fay, run into L'Fay and examine a group of about four Shadowmen. <br>
<br>
I know they're faster than SoW.  I wonder if Ice Comet will work well.  <br>
<br>
One IC and the Shadowman is dead, dead, dead.  Awesome!  Heh.  The pet is still alive and agro's me if I get in their path, so I have to burn mana on two pets.<br>
<br>
Okay.  What?  I see a rapier on that Shadowman!  Ice Comet, run up loot, woot!  Hero for the day!  Third Shadowman.  I looted with three still up.  I got nuked for 149, but that's nothing Spankda can't handle.<br>
<br>
Guild chick got her boots.  Point here really is that if you're farming or shadowman hunting, Ice Comet will kill a shadowman in one hit.  Very, very nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/4/01 7:41:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spankda Update -- Level 51</span><hr size=1> No one replied to my 51 update.  Still 51.  I'm under a full orange from 52 now, though.  I've been working a bit on trade skills (mainly smithing) because I'll need that for fine plate for some watchman stuff for tinkering.<br>
<br>
Does the trade skill cycle ever end?<br>
<br>
I'm just showing off my newest digs.  I've had them a while.  I look swankda.  I think.<br>
