I'll reply 8-)<br>
<br>
I have my CS tooth now but haven't ventured there for the purpose of quadding yet.<br>
<br>
I worked thru 51 at the well-known spirocs. Fortunately for me my prime time 8pm - 12 falls at about 3am -7am PST. Often I was the only one there or only one of 2 people there, which made it too easy, to basically flux 4 blues, occasionally a green (which still gave xp normally).<br>
<br>
Anyone who has done any kiting will find these so easy at 51. Pillar of Frost really does bring back the ability I enjoyed mid 30's with CoF. Normally finish a kite with 30-50m depending on resists and adds, Harvest, med up, do my laundry, come back... etc.  A real no-brainer and only 1 wanderer to worry about, so as long as you stay off their path, no hassles. Doing about 4 hours a night, I got thru most of 51 in about 2 nights. <br>
<br>
Interested in checking out CS soon, perhaps this weekend.<br>
<br>
Aazuar, Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/5/01 10:01:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spankda Update -- Level 51</span><hr size=1> Spankda!<br>
